Can't say there are any, writing from other writers is always either super stilted, or is so far up its own ass with whatever it has going on it's obnoxious to read. Or both.
I'm extremely picky* with how things are written to the point the only things I tend to re-read now are stuff I've written in the past, and even then I'm reading it thinking the writing doesn't flow properly and I want to make minor tweaks to the writing, every time.

*For example, 3rd person is out the window from the start, because as far as I can tell it's absolutely impossible to make it not feel juvenile to read. For another example, how exactly dragons are handled (basically animals or just subservient to humans, dragonriding AGAIN, etc.), the universe mechanics just being stupid, the writing being obtuse for no good reason other than ego stroking, etc.
